a1:TemplateCategory.Name: 1-key
a1:TemplateCategory.Comments: These templates are composed of a single key. If any of these templates conflict with single letter variables that you use frequently, you can move them individually to a disabled folder, or you can disable all templates in this category by clicking the green check box to the left of the "1-key" category node.

a1:TemplateCategory.Name: Comments
a1:TemplateCategory.Comments: These templates add comments to the code. Nearly all of these templates start with the "/" character.

a1:TemplateCategory.Name: Program Blocks
a1:TemplateCategory.Comments: Templates in this category generate program blocks that can be used inside methods and property accessors.

a1:TemplateCategory.Name: Setting Values
a1:TemplateCategory.Comments: Templates in this category all begin with the letter "S" and work with an identifier copied to the clipboard

a1:TemplateCategory.Name: System
a1:TemplateCategory.Comments: This category contains system templates that are referenced by other templates. Changing these will impact all templates with aliases to them.

a1:Template._Comment: /* */ Comment

a1:TemplateCategory.Name: Misc.
a1:TemplateCategory.Comments: Miscellaneous comment templates, including "/t" (Translate) and "/dnt" (Do Not Translate), used to mark strings for translation.

a1:TemplateCategory.Name: Tasks
a1:TemplateCategory.Comments: Templates for adding TODO tasks and marking problem areas of the code.

a1:TemplateCategory.Name: Else blocks
a1:TemplateCategory.Comments: Templates in this category generate Else blocks. Nearly all of these templates start with the letter "L". Many of these templates string together powerful combos. For example, "sn" sets the identifier on the clipboard to null. "lsn" creates the "else" keyword, and then sets the identifier on the clipboard to null.

a1:TemplateCategory.Name: Flow
a1:TemplateCategory.Comments: Templates in this category generate code that controls program flow. This includes loops (while, for, foreach, etc.), switch statements, and flow breakage (e.g., throw exceptions, return, break, continue, etc.).

a1:TemplateCategory.Name: If blocks
a1:TemplateCategory.Comments: Templates in this category generate if blocks. Most start with "if", however a few start with "in", which will lead to "if (!...)" blocks.

a1:TemplateCategory.Name: Returning Values
a1:TemplateCategory.Comments: Templates in this category return values. These templates all start with the letter "r", and end with one or two characters that describe the value to return. For example, "rf" returns false.

a1:TemplateCategory.Name: try...
a1:TemplateCategory.Comments: Templates in this category generate try/finally and try/catch blocks. These templates all start with the letter "t".
